I had found out about this restaurant from a piece in New-Yorker. I live in DC area, from where I went to Brooklyn to check this restaurant, and it definitely lived up to my expectations.  I would never imagine that in the US, I could visit an Azerbaijani restaurant, where food was just as good as in Azerbaijan. I with my friend ordered traditional Azeri “shepherd salad”, borscht, kharcho, lula kabab, which were served with hot bread. Everything was just super delicious. The kabab chef did a really amazing job, and I had a chance to thank him personally in the end. We ordered tea in the end and got served a traditional Azeri tea set (tea, lemon, cube sugar and a varenye of our choice). It was great as well.  I will definitely go back to this restaurant next time I visit NYC. Just this restaurant is worth a whole trip from DC to NYC. Hoping to see them become a chain and expand to DC area as well.
